A positive integer is given. Get an array of its digits, written in reverse order (from the last digit to the first).

Write a function called arrayOfDigits that takes the number n as an argument and returns an array of its digits in reverse order. 
The use of the split, reverse methods is prohibited. Use a do while loop in your solution.

Examples:

arrayOfDigits (123456) should return [6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1];
arrayOfDigits (1000) should return [0, 0, 0, 1];
arrayOfDigits (1) should return [1].


Solution:

function arrayOfDigits(n){
  let arr = [];
  let lastn;
  do {
     lastn = n % 10;
     arr.push(lastn);
     n = (n - lastn) / 10;
  } while (n > 0);
  return arr;     
}
